definitions: happening or produced without being planned or meant to occur
examples: The unintentional error caused confusion in the report
Her unintentional comment hurt his feelings deeply

definitions: not interested in or concerned about something or someone
examples: She seemed uninterested in the conversation about politics
The uninterested students stared blankly at their phones

definitions: not arousing curiosity or interest due to being dull or tedious
examples: The speaker gave an uninteresting presentation about tax law
She found the movie uninteresting and left halfway through

definitions: continuing without a break or pause in between parts or events
examples: The baby slept for eight uninterrupted hours last night
We need uninterrupted time to finish this project

definitions: arriving or acting without having been asked or invited to do so
examples: Several uninvited guests showed up at the wedding reception
His uninvited advice was not well received by anyone

definitions: not connected with or taking part in an activity or situation
examples: She remained uninvolved in the office politics and drama
The uninvolved bystanders watched the argument from a distance

definitions: organized into or belonging to a labor union for collective bargaining
examples: The unionized workers negotiated for better healthcare benefits
Most employees at the unionized factory earn higher wages

definitions: designed to be suitable for both males and females equally
examples: The store sells unisex clothing in neutral colors and styles
They installed unisex bathrooms in the new office building

definitions: forming a single or unified entity rather than separate parts
examples: The country adopted a unitary system of government
The unitary structure simplified the decision-making process significantly

definitions: not based on or behaving according to principles of justice or fairness
examples: The court overturned the unjust verdict after new evidence emerged
Many protested against the unjust treatment of minority groups

definitions: not able to be shown as right or reasonable under any circumstances
examples: The committee found his actions completely unjustifiable
Such unjustifiable violence shocked the entire community

definitions: not shown to be right or reasonable based on available evidence
examples: Her fears proved to be completely unjustified
The unjustified criticism damaged his professional reputation

definitions: having a messy or disheveled appearance from lack of care
examples: His unkempt hair suggested he had just woken up
The unkempt garden was overgrown with weeds and vines

definitions: inconsiderate and harsh toward others in behavior or words
examples: It was unkind to laugh at his honest mistake
Her unkind remarks left him feeling hurt and confused

definitions: not able to be known or understood by human minds
examples: The ultimate fate of the universe remains unknowable
Some mysteries of consciousness may be forever unknowable

definitions: not aware of or not having knowledge about something
examples: The unknowing participants were part of a psychology experiment
She was an unknowing accomplice to the elaborate scheme

definitions: not conforming to or permitted by law or rules
examples: The court ruled that the search was unlawful
Unlawful parking will result in your vehicle being towed

definitions: containing no lead compounds, especially referring to gasoline or paint
examples: Most modern cars require unleaded gasoline to run properly
The old house needed repainting with unleaded paint

definitions: not having an official license or permit required by law
examples: The unlicensed driver was arrested during a routine traffic stop
Operating an unlicensed business can result in heavy fines

definitions: not limited or restricted in terms of number, quantity, or extent
examples: The phone plan includes unlimited data and text messaging
Children seem to have unlimited energy for playing games

definitions: not included in a list, directory, or catalog of items
examples: She keeps her phone number unlisted for privacy reasons
The unlisted stock cannot be traded on major exchanges

definitions: having had cargo or contents removed from a vehicle or container
having no bullets or ammunition in a firearm
examples: The unloaded truck returned to the warehouse for more deliveries
Workers quickly unloaded the ship at the busy port
Always check that the gun is unloaded before cleaning
The police confirmed the weapon was unloaded during arrest

definitions: not fastened or secured with a lock or similar device
examples: She found the door unlocked when she arrived home
The unlocked phone allowed easy access to all apps

definitions: having, bringing, or resulting from bad luck or misfortune
examples: He was unlucky to miss the winning lottery by one number
Friday the thirteenth is considered an unlucky day

definitions: not yet made or constructed into a finished form
having bedclothes that are not neatly arranged after use
examples: The unmade road was rough and full of potholes
Several unmade decisions still needed the board's attention
She left her unmade bed in a rush to work
The hotel room had unmade beds when we arrived

definitions: impossible or very difficult to manage, control, or deal with effectively
examples: Her thick hair becomes unmanageable in humid weather
The project grew unmanageable without proper planning and resources

definitions: not having or needing a human operator or crew present
examples: The military uses unmanned drones for reconnaissance missions
An unmanned spacecraft successfully landed on the distant planet

definitions: not having any marks, signs, or distinguishing features
examples: Police often use unmarked cars for surveillance operations
The unmarked grave contained remains from the Civil War

definitions: not married or not having a spouse
examples: The unmarried couple decided to buy a house together
She remained unmarried throughout her successful career

definitions: having no equal in quality or extent
not corresponding or forming a matched set
examples: Her unmatched skill in negotiation impressed the board members
The restaurant offers unmatched views of the city skyline
He wore unmatched socks to the important business meeting
The unmatched dishes gave the table an eclectic look

definitions: not able to be mistaken for anything else due to being very distinctive
examples: Her unmistakable laugh could be heard across the room
The unmistakable smell of coffee filled the morning air

definitions: absolute and unqualified, often used to emphasize how bad something is
examples: The project was an unmitigated disaster from start to finish
His unmitigated gall in asking for a raise shocked everyone

definitions: remaining in the original form without any changes or alterations
examples: The software runs on unmodified hardware from ten years ago
Scientists studied the unmodified genetic sequence for comparison

definitions: not affected by emotion or persuasion
remaining in the same physical position
examples: She remained unmoved by his passionate plea for forgiveness
The judge seemed unmoved by the defendant's tears
The heavy furniture remained unmoved during the earthquake
The statue has been unmoved for over a century

definitions: not identified by name or having no name given
examples: An unnamed source leaked the confidential information to reporters
The unnamed river flows through several remote villages

definitions: contrary to the ordinary course of nature
not spontaneous or genuine but forced and artificial
examples: The unnatural blue color of the lake indicated pollution
Scientists investigated the unnatural behavior of the animals
Her unnatural smile made everyone feel uncomfortable
He spoke in an unnatural voice during the interview

definitions: not needed or more than is needed for a particular purpose
examples: Avoid unnecessary expenses during these difficult financial times
The teacher eliminated unnecessary homework to reduce student stress

definitions: not necessary or not required for a particular purpose
examples: Please remove all unneeded items from your desk
The company laid off unneeded workers during the recession

definitions: made to feel worried, discouraged, or less confident about something
examples: The strange noises in the house left her completely unnerved
He was unnerved by the interviewer's aggressive questioning style

definitions: causing one to feel worried, disconcerted, or loss of confidence
examples: The unnerving silence in the forest made them walk faster
She found his constant staring unnerving and uncomfortable

definitions: not seen or noticed by anyone despite being present
examples: The error went unnoticed until the final review stage
She slipped out of the party unnoticed by other guests

definitions: not marked with or assigned identifying numbers
too numerous to be counted
examples: The unnumbered pages made the document difficult to organize
Store the files in unnumbered folders arranged alphabetically
Unnumbered stars filled the clear desert sky that night
She had unnumbered reasons to be grateful for her family

definitions: not seen or noticed by anyone while happening or being present
examples: The thief entered the building unobserved through a side door
Many chemical reactions occur unobserved at the molecular level

definitions: not blocked or impeded by any obstacles in the way
examples: The apartment has unobstructed views of the ocean
Emergency exits must remain unobstructed at all times

definitions: not conspicuous or attracting attention in an unwelcome or intrusive way
examples: The security cameras were designed to be unobtrusive
She preferred unobtrusive jewelry for everyday wear

definitions: not occupied by anyone or empty of people
examples: The unoccupied house had been for sale for months
She found an unoccupied table in the crowded restaurant

definitions: not officially authorized or confirmed by proper authorities
examples: The unofficial vote count showed a very close race
According to unofficial sources, the merger will happen soon

definitions: not opened or still sealed in original packaging
examples: The unopened letter sat on her desk for weeks
Return any unopened products for a full refund

definitions: not opposed or challenged by anyone in competition or conflict
examples: She ran unopposed for the position of class president
The motion passed unopposed at the board meeting

definitions: not organized or arranged in a systematic or orderly way
examples: His unorganized desk made it hard to find important documents
The unorganized protest quickly lost momentum and dispersed
